    .recipe-container
      h1.recipe-title Palak Paneer Recipe
      p.recipe-text A popular North Indian dish made with spinach and cottage cheese.

      h2.ingredients-title Ingredients
      ul.ingredient-list
        li 2 cups spinach, blanched and pureed
        li 200g cottage cheese (paneer), cubed
        li 2 tomatoes, pureed
        li 1 onion, finely chopped
        li 1 tsp ginger-garlic paste
        li 1 green chili, chopped
        li 1/2 tsp cumin seeds
        li 1/2 tsp turmeric powder
        li 1/2 tsp red chili powder
        li 1/2 tsp garam masala
        li 1/4 cup heavy cream
        li Salt to taste
        li 2 tbsp oil or ghee

      h2.procedure-title Procedure
      p.procedure-step Heat oil or ghee in a pan. Add cumin seeds and let them splutter.
      p.procedure-step Add chopped onions and sauté until they turn golden brown.
      p.procedure-step Add ginger-garlic paste and green chili. Sauté for a minute.
      p.procedure-step Add tomato puree, turmeric powder, red chili powder, and salt. Cook until the mixture thickens and the oil separates.
      p.procedure-step Add spinach puree and cook for a few minutes.
      p.procedure-step Add cubed paneer and mix gently.
      p.procedure-step Add garam masala and heavy cream. Mix well and simmer for a couple of minutes.
      p.procedure-step Palak Paneer is ready to be served. Enjoy with naan or rice.

    
